      "writtenOn": "2020-03-19T18:30:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I added the pointer-keyed map because the step names are derived from log output, which means there\u0027s no guarantee we won\u0027t orphan a step by accident.  I didn\u0027t want to cause a failure for the same reason.  Removed childrenByName and changed FindChild to use Step.name instead, which will be less efficient, but I suspect it won\u0027t matter much in practice.  Added comments to FindStep and FindChild indicating that they shouldn\u0027t be used if the step names aren\u0027t expected to be unique.",
